== Books

[https://www.facebook.com/yahasgaruna/posts/10152677116931285 This post] gives a rough idea of the kind of books I am interested in. Currently, I am hugely into the works of Jim Butcher (/The Dresden Files/, /Codex Alera/, /The Cinder Spires/), Max Gladstone (/The Craft Sequence/, /Bookburners/, /This Is How You Lose The Time War/), N.K. Jemisin (/The Inheritance Trilogy/, /The Broken Earth Trilogy/), and  Brandon Sanderson (/The Cosmere Sequence/, including /Mistborn/, /Warbreaker/ and /The Stormlight Archive/). About a year ago, I also fell in love with /The Vorkosigan Saga/ by Lois McMaster Bujold. 

While epic fantasy doorstoppers are my first love, I've recently started a foray into fantasy novellas and short novels, especially those published by [https://publishing.tor.com Tor.com publishing].

I was also a major fan of the Star Wars Expanded Universe (now known as Star Wars: Legends). Grand Admiral Thrawn is my favourite Star Wars character, Timothy Zahn is my favourite Star Wars writer and Luke Skywalker+Mara Jade is my [http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OneTruePairing OTP]. As far as I'm concerned, if Mara no longer exists in the newfangled Disney canon, then the newfangled Disney canon does not exist for me. (Okay, maybe that's not precisely true...)

I love comic books, though I now largely consume them through adaptations only. My favourite comic book run is Geoff Johns and Peter Tomasi's on Green Lantern; /Green Lantern: Rebirth/ was one of my two gateways into superhero comics. The other gateway comic was Jeph Loeb's run on /Superman\/Batman/. My favourite mini-series is probably Grant Morrison's /All-Star Superman/. In general, I'm a DC guy, but I really adored Greg Pak's run on /The Incredible Hercules/ (a Marvel publication). If I get to see a cinematic adaptation of /JLA\/Avengers/, I will die a man satisfied with his life.

In recent times (especially since the release of /Avengers: Infinity War/ and /Avengers: Endgame/), I've been reconsidering my loyalty to DC.

My favourite book series of all time is /The Wheel of Time/, by Robert Jordan, though my favourite author is probably Isaac Asimov. The question of which is my favourite book is much more difficult to answer so I'm not going to attempt to do it; however, /Good Omens: The Nice and Accurate Prophecies of Agnes Nutter, Witch/ by Terry Pratchett and Neil Gaiman is probably up there somewhere on the list (you should watch the delightful adaptation of it on Amazon Prime!).

