== Games
Growing up, except for the short time I owned a PlayStation 2, the only videogames I used to play were real-time strategy games. My favourite videogame is probably Age of Mythology, and I adore the entire Age of Empires sequence. I also loved Warcraft III, and Blizzard's insistence towards no longer making Warcraft RTS games is my biggest gripe with the World of Warcraft MMORPG. I stopped playing videogames regularly around the same time I retired my PlayStation (that is, around 2008).

I love playing cards; in particular, I like rummy, 29 and hearts. In general, I prefer trick-taking games.

These days, I am really into modern boardgames. I enjoy some classics (particularly /Cluedo/, /Stratego/, /Risk/ and /Scrabble/), but I mostly prefer modern Euro games, with a sprinkling of Ameritrash and a party game or two. 

My favourite modern game is [https://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/209418/dominion-second-edition /Dominion/]; I play [https://dominion.games online] with the handle [http://dominion.lauxnet.com/scavenger/?user=yahas yahas]. I've recently started playing [https://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/120677/terra-mystica /Terra Mystica/] on [https://terra.snellman.net snellman], again with the handle [https://terra.snellman.net/player/yahas yahas]. I also play a bunch of other games (particularly, /Dice Forge/, /Kingdomino/, /Puerto Rico/, /Siam/, /7 Wonders/, /Stone Age/, /Takenoko/, /Tokaido/, /Carcassone/, and /Through the Ages/) on [https://boardgamearena.com Board Game Arena], again, with the handle yahas. Offline, my favourite 2-player game is /7 Wonders: Duel/, my favourite social deduction game is /Avalon/ and my favourite party game is /Codenames/. It's much much harder to pin down my favourite heavy game, so I won't even try - but I like /Scythe/ enough to actual own it, instead of just playing other people's copies. The list of games I physically own are on my [https://boardgamegeek.com/user/yahas/ BGG profile].

I play IRL with the [https://facebook.com/groups/BoardGamersOfDelhi Board Gamers of Delhi] whenever I am in Delhi.

One of the best games I have played, which requires no resources but people to play, is [contact.html /Contact/].

== TV Shows and Movies

I don't watch a lot of movies, but when I do, they're almost exclusively either adaptations from other media, or they're rom-coms. I am a big fan of the /Marvel Cinematic Universe/, and the list of the movies I keep rewatching again includes /10 Things I Hate About You/ and /Begin Again/.

Two TV shows that had a huge impact on me as a kid were /Chuck/ and /Psych/. /Chuck/ is possibly single-handedly responsible for my early forays into alternate or indie rock. I was also very into cartoons (both western and anime) as a kid, some favourites include, the entire /DC Animated Universe/ (particularly /Justice League/), /Cardcaptor Sakura/, /Digimon/ and /Fullmetal Alchemist/. I really want to restart watching them (especially /Young Justice/), but I really haven't come around to it.

These days I don't have too much time to watch too many shows, but I really enjoyed the first few seasons of the /Arrowverse/ and the Marvel Netflix TV shows.

One modern web television series that I absolutely adore is the /The Lizzie Bennet Diaries/. It's available for free online, and is a New Media adaptation of /Pride and Prejudice/.

== Music
When I was younger, I largely listened only to rock and alternate rock. I have since expanded my tastes to country, progressive rock and some pop. [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=juvwlEO-x2o /3 Rounds and a Sound/] by Blind Pilot is my favourite alt rock song, the Coke Studio (Pakistan) rendition of [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=a18py61_F_w /Tajdar-e-Haram/] by Atif Aslam is my favourite song in a Hindustani language, A.R. Rahman is my favourite Bollywood musician, [https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLbIAuSOQuB99D5mzvDuu1P2fKh_v6qPIe /Begin Again/] is my favourite original soundtrack from a motion picture and [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A_MjCqQoLLA /Hey Jude/] is my favourite song by the Beatles.

My current most listened to song is [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Orw-JPVXhIk /Too Repressed - explicit/] by Sometymes Why.

== History and Mythology
History and mythology are my first and second love (most likely because of the fact that they are the respective subjects of the games I played most in my childhood, namely /Age of Empires/ and /Age of Mythology/). [https://www.youtube.com/user/crashcourse /Crash Course/] is a good place to start learning about these fascinating subjects.

